{"id": 34, "ts": 1778799554.8453982, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "I\u2019ve gathered the missing pieces on teamwork and communication:\n- **Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 No information is available about his teamwork or communication abilities from any other agent.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 No specific teamwork data, but the communication notes describe him as pretentious, sometimes using the wrong tone, and making nasty remarks toward colleagues.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 Explicitly noted to \u201cput concern for others above everything,\u201d which supports strong teamwork. However, he also has difficulty communicating ideas and is regarded as egocentric, both of which hinder effective crew interaction.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 No information is available about his teamwork or communication abilities.\nConsidering the full set of criteria:\n- **Technical and cognitive competence** is strongest in Candidate\u202fA (anticipates danger, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision) and also solid in Candidate\u202fD (problem\u2011solving, concentration). Candidate\u202fC is good at rapid decision\u2011making and technology, while Candidate\u202fB has good weather assessment and computer skills.\n- **Reliability/Responsibility**: Candidate\u202fC is 100\u202f% reliable; Candidate\u202fD takes responsibility seriously; Candidate\u202fA shows leadership; Candidate\u202fB is very conscientious.\n- **Calmness, judgment, pressure handling**: Candidate\u202fB handles stress well; Candidate\u202fC stays calm in crises; Candidate\u202fD responds adequately to unexpected events; Candidate\u202fA\u2019s ability to anticipate danger suggests good judgment.\n- **Decision\u2011making**: Candidate\u202fC makes quick correct decisions; Candidate\u202fA\u2019s ability to see complex connections supports sound decisions; Candidate\u202fB and D also perform well.\n- **Teamwork & communication**: Candidate\u202fC has