{"id": 78, "ts": 1778799766.2256377, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "I agree that Candidate\u202fA offers the strongest combination of technical and cognitive abilities for long\u2011distance piloting\u2014anticipating dangerous situations, seeing complex connections, excellent spatial vision, and very good leadership. The only notable gaps are the missing data on A\u2019s teamwork and communication skills, and the interpersonal notes that A can be a \u201cshow\u2011off\u201d and resistant to new ideas. These traits are not, by themselves, safety\u2011critical, but confirming that A can communicate effectively with the crew would remove the remaining uncertainty.\nConversely, Candidate\u202fB has a safety\u2011critical weakness (weak memory for numbers) and consistently negative communication behavior. Candidate\u202fC, while strong in rapid decision\u2011making and teamwork intent, has clear communication deficits and a lack of willingness to pursue further education. Candidate\u202fD shows excellent concentration, problem\u2011solving, and responsibility, but we have no information on his teamwork or communication, and his \u201cknow\u2011it\u2011all\u201d attitude and hot temper could jeopardize crew cohesion.\nGiven the current evidence, Candidate\u202fA remains the best overall fit, but I would like to close the remaining information gap: **Does any agent have any information\u2014positive or negative\u2014about Candidate\u202fD\u2019s teamwork and communication abilities?** This would help confirm whether D\u2019s strong problem\u2011solving can be safely paired with crew interaction.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate A\"}"}
